<section id="Adding_a_Repository" remap="TID_15374">
	<title>Adding a Repository</title>
	<para>
		To refresh a repository for more detailed information, add it to your VMDB first. The VMDB requires a universal naming convention (UNC) network path to the repository.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Add a Repository</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to menu:Infrastructure[Repositories].
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>(Configuration)</guibutton>, then click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1848.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>(Add a new Repository)</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				In <guilabel>Basic Information</guilabel>, enter a <guilabel>Name</guilabel> and a UNC network <guilabel>Path</guilabel> to the repository location.
			</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/2240.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guilabel>Save</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>